.TH "radeon_ring_lock" 9 "radeon_ring_lock" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
radeon_ring_lock \- lock the ring and allocate space on it
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" radeon_ring_lock
.BI "(struct radeon_device *rdev "  ","
.BI "struct radeon_ring *ring "  ","
.BI "unsigned ndw "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "rdev" 12
radeon_device pointer
.IP "ring" 12
radeon_ring structure holding ring information
.IP "ndw" 12
number of dwords to allocate in the ring buffer
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Lock the ring and allocate \fIndw\fP dwords in the ring buffer
(all asics).
Returns 0 on success, error on failure.
